THE RADISH.

Indeed the soil of Paraguay seems peculiarly savourable to radishes‚ which grow every where to an amazing size, and are very pernicious to wheat, by choking up the fields like tares.

The European nasturtium is almost unknown to the whole of Paraguay3 though the garden,

SAFFRON.

The European saffron is found in no part of Paraguay. The American, which is saffron in name and appearance only, is not used for sea- soning food, but for dying things os a yellow colour.
